Class Queue<E>

java.lang.Object
  dat1.Queue<E>

public class Queue<E>
extends java.lang.Object

The Queue class implements a first-in first-out (FIFO) data structure.

Items are added to (enqueued in) the Queue using enqueue() and removed (dequeued) from it using dequeue(). isEmpty() is provided as a means to determine whether or not the Queue is empty.

Author:
K. Atas
